WEBVTT

00:02.611 --> 00:04.526
Previously onIn the Dark...Tyson. Help!

00:04.569 --> 00:06.223
JULES:
I know Darnell didn't do it.

00:06.267 --> 00:09.052
How?
Because he was
with me that night.

00:09.096 --> 00:10.836
I'm just trying to figure out
how we both got popped

00:10.880 --> 00:12.229
on the same thing

00:12.273 --> 00:14.275
and you got out in,
what, an hour.

00:14.318 --> 00:15.624
JULES:
We think whoever
killed Tyson

00:15.667 --> 00:18.627
sent you and Darnell James
those texts remotely.

00:18.670 --> 00:20.411
So you can track them
and you can figure out

00:20.455 --> 00:22.674
who hacked into his account
or whatever?

00:22.718 --> 00:24.285
JULES:
Whoever hacked
into Tyson's account

00:24.328 --> 00:26.548
was using their Wi-Fi.

00:26.591 --> 00:28.724
I saw someone meeting with Nia.

00:28.767 --> 00:30.856
I recognized their gun holster. We all

00:30.900 --> 00:33.729
have the same one. I think
the person who's framing you

00:33.772 --> 00:35.861
is a cop. I'm crazy about you.

00:35.905 --> 00:37.515
I don't know who it is,

00:37.559 --> 00:39.996
but I swear to God, I'm gonna
find this son of a bitch.

00:42.477 --> 00:45.436
[crow cawing]

00:45.480 --> 00:48.526
Chicago PD. I'd like
to speak with Nia Bailey.

00:48.570 --> 00:50.224
Come in.

00:50.267 --> 00:52.965
Take off your shoes.

00:53.009 --> 00:54.532
[door closes]

00:54.576 --> 00:56.186
Nia.

00:56.230 --> 00:58.928
Detective Riley.

00:58.971 --> 01:01.974
I'd like to ask you
a few questions.

01:02.018 --> 01:03.715
You mind?

01:03.759 --> 01:05.717
Have a seat.

01:05.761 --> 01:07.719
Can I get you a
drink or something?

01:07.763 --> 01:08.938
I'm good.

01:08.981 --> 01:09.982
There was a, uh...

01:10.026 --> 01:12.028
a shooting
at the liquor store

01:12.072 --> 01:14.552
on Shields Avenue
last Wednesday.

01:14.596 --> 01:16.902
Cashier identified the driver
as one of your rivals.

01:16.946 --> 01:18.165
Rivals?

01:18.208 --> 01:20.036
In my dry cleaning business?

01:20.080 --> 01:22.299
Honey, my only rivals
are washing machines.

01:22.343 --> 01:24.997
[chuckles]

01:25.041 --> 01:27.739
How you holding up, baby?

01:27.783 --> 01:29.524
Excuse me?

01:29.567 --> 01:32.179
I mean, if I lost
my wife in a car wreck,

01:32.222 --> 01:35.182
I don't know if I'd be back
to work so soon.

01:36.357 --> 01:37.967
That's none of your business.

01:38.010 --> 01:39.708
How's your daughter doing?

01:39.751 --> 01:41.101
She still in the hospital?

01:41.144 --> 01:43.842
How do you know about that?

01:43.886 --> 01:45.583
You know,
my nephew has bone cancer.

01:45.627 --> 01:48.369
I mean, no child should
suffer the way he has.

01:48.412 --> 01:50.936
And from what I know
about the CPD health plan,

01:50.980 --> 01:52.416
the surgeries
your daughter needs

01:52.460 --> 01:54.157
will put you
well over your annual limit.

01:54.201 --> 01:56.986
Let me guess,
you'll pay for the surgery

01:57.029 --> 01:58.857
if we drop the case
we're building against you.

01:58.901 --> 02:00.642
It's never going to happen.

02:00.685 --> 02:02.818
It's just a tip here and there.
It's nothing major.

02:02.861 --> 02:05.081
Nothing will ever
trace back to you.

02:05.125 --> 02:07.214
You ain't ever gonna talk
to anybody.

02:07.257 --> 02:11.740
All our transactions go through
a locker at the train station.

02:11.783 --> 02:14.699
Oh, and...

02:16.745 --> 02:19.139
[paper tears]

02:22.751 --> 02:25.057
Here's
your liquor store shooter.

02:30.019 --> 02:32.456
[laughing][sighs]

02:32.500 --> 02:34.241
Oh, there's no way.

02:34.284 --> 02:35.981
Yeah.No.

02:36.025 --> 02:38.984
Listen, I--
She wanted to kiss me.

02:39.028 --> 02:41.030
I said, "I'm only 12."[laughs]

02:41.073 --> 02:43.032
And then,
and then she kissed me,

02:43.075 --> 02:45.034
and I was like,
"Oh, I get how it works now."

02:45.077 --> 02:46.992
No. No, no.
[laughing][laughs]

02:47.036 --> 02:49.473
Ah.

02:49.517 --> 02:51.693
Wait, you are
not gonna believe this.

02:51.736 --> 02:53.216
What?[clears throat]

02:53.260 --> 02:56.828
The, uh, sun is up.

02:56.872 --> 02:58.221
Are you serious?

02:58.265 --> 02:59.440
Yeah. Here.

02:59.483 --> 03:01.006
Oh, my God.Come here.

03:01.050 --> 03:02.660
What?

03:04.271 --> 03:06.229
Feel that?

03:07.361 --> 03:08.840
Mm-hmm.

03:08.884 --> 03:10.320
[chuckles softly]

03:10.364 --> 03:13.193
Yeah, I actually can.

03:16.979 --> 03:20.765
I can't even believe
I'm gonna say this, but...

03:20.809 --> 03:23.768
I think the only silver
lining about this year

03:23.812 --> 03:26.075
is that it led me to you.

03:28.773 --> 03:30.253
Wow.

03:30.297 --> 03:33.952
I did not know
you were such a sap.

03:33.996 --> 03:36.477
[snorts] Shut up![chuckles]

03:36.520 --> 03:38.043
Oh, it's very romantic.[laughs]

03:38.087 --> 03:39.131
Everything you say
is very romantic.

03:39.175 --> 03:40.176
Fine, I take it back.

03:40.220 --> 03:41.395
No. Don't. Can't.

03:41.438 --> 03:43.440
♪

03:49.533 --> 03:52.014
Since when do you take
things slow?

03:52.057 --> 03:54.451
I don't know. Since
I don't want to mess things up.

03:54.495 --> 03:57.367
Unlike stupid Max, Dean
might actually be good for me.

03:57.411 --> 04:00.283
I just want the first time
we have sex to be in, like...

04:00.327 --> 04:02.154
a lesbian way.

04:02.198 --> 04:03.591
Multiple orgasms?

04:03.634 --> 04:05.593
[laughs]:
No, shut up. Like...

04:05.636 --> 04:07.856
like how you always want it
to be special or whatever.

04:07.899 --> 04:09.553
You know?Well, you
could go away

04:09.597 --> 04:11.990
for a romantic weekend.

04:12.034 --> 04:14.906
That's a super gay way
to do it for the first time.

04:14.950 --> 04:17.082
Yeah.
[chuckles]No, no, no.

04:17.126 --> 04:19.084
Why am I literally
the only one

04:19.128 --> 04:21.043
who does anything around
here while you guys get

04:21.086 --> 04:23.045
to just sit around, talking
about your sordid love lives

04:23.088 --> 04:25.352
and whether you want tacos
or poke bowls for lunch?

04:25.395 --> 04:28.703
Just work!
Please, I'm begging you.

04:29.747 --> 04:31.009
Geez.

04:31.053 --> 04:32.272
What's with him?

04:32.315 --> 04:33.621
I don't know.

04:33.664 --> 04:35.927
Probably his period
or something.

04:35.971 --> 04:38.234
[indistinct chatter]

04:44.109 --> 04:45.459
♪

04:52.248 --> 04:54.250
[clears throat]

05:01.997 --> 05:04.956
You look like you got
less sleep than I did.

05:05.000 --> 05:06.349
[chuckles]

05:06.393 --> 05:07.916
Yeah.

05:07.959 --> 05:09.004
[coffee pouring]

05:09.047 --> 05:10.919
Jules?

05:10.962 --> 05:12.181
Talk to me.

05:12.224 --> 05:13.965
[quietly]:
Not here.

05:14.009 --> 05:15.837
Let's-let's go outside.

05:18.100 --> 05:20.929
[siren wailing]

05:20.972 --> 05:23.845
Okay, what is
going on?

05:23.888 --> 05:26.369
There's a dirty cop here.

05:26.413 --> 05:30.634
What? Where-where
did you hear that?

05:30.678 --> 05:33.071
I followed Nia
last night.

05:33.115 --> 05:36.423
And I saw her talking
to one of our own.

05:36.466 --> 05:38.990
You saw who
she was talking to?

05:39.034 --> 05:42.472
I couldn't see his face, but
I-I could see his holster.

05:42.516 --> 05:47.477
So, s-someone here
is in with Nia Bailey?

05:47.521 --> 05:51.002
I mean, I-I guess
it explains how she got off.

05:52.352 --> 05:56.051
Or how Darnell was framed.

05:56.094 --> 05:57.531
Wait, you...
[scoffs]

05:57.574 --> 06:00.055
Are you thinking
that Nia told this cop

06:00.098 --> 06:02.013
to frame Darnell
for Parker's murder?

06:02.057 --> 06:04.799
I don't think Nia would
want to put Darnell away.

06:04.842 --> 06:06.409
He's one of her best guys.

06:06.453 --> 06:08.933
[sighs]
I'm just...

06:08.977 --> 06:13.242
I'm wondering if this dirty cop
might be covering for himself.

06:15.113 --> 06:16.724
Obviously, whoever it was,

06:16.767 --> 06:18.987
if he had time to meet
with Nia, then he wasn't...

06:19.030 --> 06:21.076
working last night.

06:21.119 --> 06:23.252
I'm gonna check the logs.

06:23.295 --> 06:27.256
Sorry, you're just-- you're
blowing my mind a little here.

06:27.299 --> 06:30.085
Uh...

06:30.128 --> 06:32.261
Okay. All right, well,
look, we're gonna have

06:32.304 --> 06:33.958
to keep our eyes peeled,
see what we can see.

06:34.002 --> 06:35.873
Um...

06:35.917 --> 06:38.659
in the meantime, Chloe has
a-a half-day from school.

06:38.702 --> 06:40.051
So may-maybe
we can all get lunch.

06:40.095 --> 06:41.444
It's my treat.

06:42.489 --> 06:43.794
Yeah.

06:43.838 --> 06:46.318
Sure.Okay.

07:01.943 --> 07:03.858
Hey.

07:05.947 --> 07:08.558
We need to talk.

07:09.646 --> 07:11.256
Okay.

07:11.300 --> 07:12.736
Oh, God.

07:12.780 --> 07:14.477
I feel like I'm gonna be
physically ill.

07:14.521 --> 07:15.522
Dude, what is
going on?

07:15.565 --> 07:17.349
[groans, exhales]

07:17.393 --> 07:20.309
Okay, you cannot
tell anyone.

07:22.746 --> 07:26.837
I have to close Guiding Hope.

07:26.881 --> 07:28.143
Hang on.

07:28.186 --> 07:30.493
Is this just you
being dramatic?

07:30.537 --> 07:32.147
I inherited so much debt, and
I just couldn't crawl out of it,

07:32.190 --> 07:33.670
especially once my mother
cut me off.

07:33.714 --> 07:35.498
Okay, how much debt?

07:35.542 --> 07:37.500
Oh, $75,000.

07:37.544 --> 07:39.676
What?Holy...

07:39.720 --> 07:41.722
That's a lot.

07:42.766 --> 07:44.725
So that's it?

07:44.768 --> 07:47.031
Guiding Hope
is, like...

07:47.075 --> 07:48.729
done?

07:48.772 --> 07:50.774
Yeah.

07:52.297 --> 07:54.735
Hey, Chloe. It's Jules.

07:54.778 --> 07:56.301
Oh, hey.

07:56.345 --> 07:57.868
How are you? You good?

07:57.912 --> 08:01.350
CHLOE:
Fine. Just working
on math homework.

08:01.393 --> 08:03.961
What's the point? My phone
literally does everything.

08:04.005 --> 08:06.573
JULES:
Your dad got off early
last night.

08:06.616 --> 08:07.791
You guys do anything fun?

08:07.835 --> 08:09.750
Yeah, we went
roller-skating.

08:09.793 --> 08:12.535
Roller-skating.
I should take my niece.

08:12.579 --> 08:13.841
Where'd you guys go?

08:13.884 --> 08:15.233
Uh, Scooters.

08:15.277 --> 08:16.757
DEAN:
Hey!

08:16.800 --> 08:18.628
Hi.We were, uh--

08:18.672 --> 08:20.108
we were just about
to leave for lunch.
Still want to come with us?

08:20.151 --> 08:22.763
No. I-I think I'm
just gonna stay here.

08:22.806 --> 08:24.025
I got a lot of work to do.

08:24.068 --> 08:25.069
Sure?

08:25.113 --> 08:26.680
Yeah. Bye, Chlo.

08:26.723 --> 08:29.421
You should totally take
your niece roller-skating.

08:29.465 --> 08:31.119
It was really fun.

08:31.162 --> 08:33.425
Will do.

08:34.905 --> 08:37.778
How did, uh, how did
roller-skating come up?

08:37.821 --> 08:40.345
She was just asking
what we did last night,

08:40.389 --> 08:42.043
'cause you had the night off.

08:44.045 --> 08:46.395
[phone ringing]

08:46.438 --> 08:48.789
FELIX:
Murphy, answer the phone!I was gonna!

08:50.791 --> 08:52.401
[sighs]

08:56.057 --> 08:58.146
Guiding Hope.

08:58.189 --> 09:00.975
DARNELL:
Murphy, don't hang up.

09:02.019 --> 09:04.195
Darnell?

09:04.239 --> 09:06.328
What do you want?

09:08.939 --> 09:10.637
You get five minutes.

09:10.680 --> 09:12.682
Did you get my letter?

09:12.726 --> 09:15.032
You sent me a letter?

09:15.076 --> 09:17.600
Look, I was framed.

09:17.644 --> 09:20.734
There is a dirty cop
who's working for Nia.

09:20.777 --> 09:22.779
What are you talking about?

09:22.823 --> 09:24.868
That's how my DNA
was planted in Tyson's car.

09:24.912 --> 09:28.655
[scoffs]
Murphy, you know me.

09:28.698 --> 09:30.831
I didn't do this.

09:30.874 --> 09:35.618
And I really need you
to help me figure out who did.

09:35.662 --> 09:38.055
Please.

09:38.099 --> 09:40.318
I don't know you.

09:40.362 --> 09:43.844
I knew Tyson.

09:43.887 --> 09:45.541
And I hope...

09:45.585 --> 09:48.588
you rot in there.

09:59.555 --> 10:01.818
[phone vibrating]

10:05.517 --> 10:08.608
Hey.Um, Darnell said
he sent me a letter.

10:08.651 --> 10:10.958
But I FaceTimed Jess,
and she said it isn't here.

10:11.001 --> 10:13.395
Do you remember
seeing-seeing anything

10:13.438 --> 10:16.006
when you-you, like, picked up
my mail the other day?

10:17.051 --> 10:18.443
Uh, no,

10:18.487 --> 10:19.662
I don't think so.
So, hey, wait,

10:19.706 --> 10:22.839
why did you talk to Darnell?

10:22.883 --> 10:23.753
I don't know.

10:23.797 --> 10:25.233
Um, I thought confronting him

10:25.276 --> 10:28.802
would make me feel better.
I just c-- I...

10:28.845 --> 10:31.674
I don't know.
He said that there's a dirty cop

10:31.718 --> 10:33.981
that framed him.
Is that...

10:34.024 --> 10:36.461
Is that a thing?
Is that possible?

10:36.505 --> 10:38.638
When someone is guilty,
they're gonna say and do

10:38.681 --> 10:40.770
anything they can
to convince you otherwise.

10:40.814 --> 10:43.425
Murphy, Darnell is lying.

10:43.468 --> 10:44.948
Yeah.

10:44.992 --> 10:47.429
No, you're right, you're right.
[clears throat]

10:47.472 --> 10:49.213
I just got to get
out of my head.

10:49.257 --> 10:50.780
Maybe we could get out of town
this weekend.

10:50.824 --> 10:52.477
That would be perfect.

10:52.521 --> 10:53.870
Yeah. Okay.

10:53.914 --> 10:56.090
I'll see you soon. Bye.

10:56.133 --> 10:57.657
Bye.

11:00.268 --> 11:01.661
[sighs]

11:04.098 --> 11:05.752
Hey, where's Becker?

11:05.795 --> 11:08.711
She took off
a couple hours ago.She say where?

11:08.755 --> 11:10.147
No.

11:16.545 --> 11:18.547
[line ringing]

11:21.463 --> 11:23.508
You have reached
Detective Becker.

11:23.552 --> 11:24.771
Please leave a message.

11:39.002 --> 11:40.787
[exhales]

11:44.747 --> 11:46.488
Well, how you been?

11:46.531 --> 11:48.751
How's Chloe?

11:48.795 --> 11:50.971
Everyone's good.

11:51.014 --> 11:52.799
It's late.

11:52.842 --> 11:54.888
What's going on?

11:54.931 --> 11:57.194
Well, I, uh, I...

11:57.238 --> 12:00.415
I thought I should
tell you that...

12:00.458 --> 12:02.896
someone is coming...

12:02.939 --> 12:05.028
for you.

12:05.072 --> 12:06.856
And...

12:06.900 --> 12:08.292
[chuckles softly]

12:08.336 --> 12:11.861
...it's not easy for
me to tell you who,

12:11.905 --> 12:13.820
because...Who?

12:18.172 --> 12:19.869
[clears throat]

12:19.913 --> 12:21.958
It's my partner.

12:23.394 --> 12:25.005
Jules Becker.

12:25.048 --> 12:27.268
And...

12:27.311 --> 12:31.663
she's got enough on you to put
you away for a very long time.

12:34.405 --> 12:36.451
A cop?

12:36.494 --> 12:39.236
That's a tough one.

12:39.280 --> 12:40.847
Oh, I know, but...

12:40.890 --> 12:42.849
look, I'm just
looking out for you,

12:42.892 --> 12:44.720
'cause that
was our deal.

12:44.764 --> 12:47.418
Right?Right.

12:47.462 --> 12:48.768
Okay.

12:50.291 --> 12:52.641
Thank you.

12:52.684 --> 12:54.034
Yeah.

12:55.078 --> 12:56.601
You hungry?

12:56.645 --> 12:57.951
I made meat loaf.

12:57.994 --> 13:00.518
Let me warm you up
a plate.

13:08.352 --> 13:10.528
How did I let this happen?

13:10.572 --> 13:12.487
I love Guiding Hope,

13:12.530 --> 13:15.620
and I ran it
into the ground.

13:16.621 --> 13:19.799
I am a total
and complete failure.

13:19.842 --> 13:21.888
Felix, I have an idea.

13:21.931 --> 13:23.411
There are

13:23.454 --> 13:25.065
no more ideas, Jess.Stop.

13:25.108 --> 13:27.719
We must accept reality now.Felix, shh. Shh.

13:27.763 --> 13:30.766
Would you just shut up for,
like, two seconds, please?

13:32.028 --> 13:35.118
I think I know where
we can get some money.

13:35.162 --> 13:36.772
["My Sharona"
by The Knack playing]

13:36.816 --> 13:38.861
MURPHY: Oh, my God, I'm feeling
so much better already.

13:38.905 --> 13:40.776
DEAN: Me, too. This was a great idea.

13:40.820 --> 13:41.821
MURPHY:
You can thank Jess.

13:41.864 --> 13:43.518
DEAN:
Ooh, I love this song.

13:43.561 --> 13:45.085
♪ Ooh, my little pretty one

13:45.128 --> 13:46.608
♪ My pretty one

13:46.651 --> 13:48.349
♪ When you gonna give me some

13:48.392 --> 13:49.916
♪ Time, Sharona

13:49.959 --> 13:51.700
♪ When you make my motor run

13:51.743 --> 13:53.571
I appreciate you
coming in on that.

13:53.615 --> 13:55.312
[stammers] What is it?

13:55.356 --> 13:57.532
♪ Line, Sharona, I don't
know all of those words ♪

13:57.575 --> 13:59.621
♪ To this song,
but I don't care ♪

13:59.664 --> 14:01.188
♪ Time... ♪ 'Cause I am in

14:01.231 --> 14:02.754
♪ The car... You don't even know it!

14:02.798 --> 14:04.452
♪ Time ♪ Sharona

14:04.495 --> 14:06.628
♪ My, my, yi, whoo!

14:06.671 --> 14:09.413
♪ M-M-M-My Sharona...

14:09.457 --> 14:11.415
You want to eat
inside, or...?

14:11.459 --> 14:13.591
Still a few hours away.
Let's just eat on the road.

14:13.635 --> 14:15.811
I will... run in.

14:15.855 --> 14:17.465
[music stops]What do you want?

14:17.508 --> 14:19.510
Mm... surprise me.

14:19.554 --> 14:21.643
I trust you.Okay.

14:21.686 --> 14:23.514
Be right back.

14:29.738 --> 14:31.609
FELIX: Where are we going?It should be
around here somewhere.

14:31.653 --> 14:33.220
Murphy said it's
next to Starshine Lake.

14:33.263 --> 14:35.396
We're taking directions
from Murphy?

14:35.439 --> 14:37.615
Also, why are we going
to Starshine Lake?

14:37.659 --> 14:39.400
What kind of lake name
is that, anyway?

14:39.443 --> 14:40.662
Actually,
it's kind of nice.

14:40.705 --> 14:41.924
Oh, my God, wait, stop.

14:41.968 --> 14:43.273
Why?Felix, stop the car!

14:43.317 --> 14:45.536
Look. Do you see that?
Do you see that?

14:45.580 --> 14:46.973
That's Max's
truck. Come on.

14:47.016 --> 14:47.974
W-Wait, no, it's freezing,

14:48.017 --> 14:49.627
and all I have is a windbreaker.

14:49.671 --> 14:51.281
Well, here's Joy's
jacket. Put that on.

14:51.325 --> 14:53.022
Absolutely not.Come on.

14:53.066 --> 14:54.632
Can you please tell me
what we are doing?

14:54.676 --> 14:56.939
Why are we looking
for Max's truck?

14:56.983 --> 15:00.464
Okay, do you remember when Max
took Murphy to that lake house?

15:00.508 --> 15:01.813
